                                <i class="fas fa-book-open me-2"></i>Our Founding Story
                            </h2>
                            <p class="lead">Friends of Uganda (FoU) is a transformative, citizen-driven national initiative designed to transcend political divisions and foster sustainable peace, unity, and national preservation during Uganda's 2026 electoral cycle and beyond.</p>
                            <p>Established in November 2025, our organization was born from a critical recognition: Uganda stands at a critical juncture as the nation approaches the 2026 general elections. While multi-party democracy remains a cornerstone of Uganda's governance framework, electoral periods have consistently exposed and exacerbated deep-seated social tensions.</p>
                            <p><strong>The Problem We Address:</strong></p>
                            <p>The political environment during election cycles is characterized by heightened political rhetoric escalating into personal attacks and hate speech, deepening social divisions exploiting ethnic and regional fault lines, erosion of national unity where political party loyalty displaces patriotic allegiance, and post-election trauma with lingering grievances that hinder national development.</p>
                            <p><strong>Our Solution:</strong></p>
                            <p>Friends of Uganda fills the critical gap: Uganda lacks a robust, non-partisan, citizen-led movement with nationwide institutional capacity to actively promote peace, facilitate cross-party dialogue, counter hate speech in real-time, and maintain sustained reconciliation efforts beyond election day.</p>
                            <p>We mobilize citizens from all walks of life to become active "friends" of their country, promoting reconciliation, rejecting divisive rhetoric, and building a cohesive society through grassroots action, strategic communication, and nationwide institutional presence.</p>
                        </div>
